/-- The restriction of scalars operation is functorial. For any `f : R ‚Üí+* S` a ring homomorphism,
* an `S`-module `M` can be considered as `R`-module by `r ‚Ä¢ m = f r ‚Ä¢ m`
* an `S`-linear map is also `R`-linear
