/-- Given an `R`-module M, consider Hom(S, M) -- the `R`-linear maps between S (as an `R`-module by
 means of restriction of scalars) and M. `S` acts on Hom(S, M) by `s ‚Ä¢ g = x ‚Ü¶ g (x ‚Ä¢ s)`
